    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-8 bg-yellow-300 text-black py-4">Communicate Frequently</h1>
    <p class="my-8 text-xl text-gray-900">
      The transition of employees working from synchronous and standardized environment to asynchronous and personalised environment is a bit alarming. According to sociometric research, frequent communication cycle proves to be more effective in building and sustaining morale of employees, in addition to their engagement. The communication platforms have made it simpler to stay in regular touch. This helps eradicate a sense of loneliness and gives a sense of being together with other colleagues. Audio and video conferences can turn their gloomy days into happy ones. The frequent communication also helps in resolving the issues at work with clear understanding and paves way in being more productive even in this unprecedented situation. Staying in regular touch not only aids in the performance of individuals at work, but also avails them in attaining a virtual companionship, which indirectly means to show up as a virtual team player.
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-8 bg-yellow-300 text-black py-4">Focus on continued learning</h1>
    <p class="my-8 text-xl text-gray-900">
